result.execSummary:
Eugene Edward Teasley Jr was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Eugene Edward Teasley Jr was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley Jr not in court, in custody.  Attorney Amanda Poznanski in court for Eugene Edward Teasley Jr.  Attorney Patrick Anderson for Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. On motion of the parties, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley Jr in court, in custody.  Attorney Amanda Poznanski in court for Eugene Edward Teasley Jr.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin.

Status conference scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley in court with attorney Amanda Poznanski.  Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley in custody.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Extradition hearing on August 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant's pro se request for order of discharge (denominated as "habeas corpus"). (Eugene Teasley #2022006581, Milwaukee County Jail, 949 N. 9th Street, Milwaukee, WI  53233).

Attorney Amanda Poznanski in court, defendant Eugene Edward Teasley not in court, in custody.  Defendant's appearance waived.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for status conference.  State is awaiting the Signed Governor's Warrant.  State's request for additional time extension for the Signed Governor's Warrant placed on the record.  Court grants 60 days additional time extension.  Case scheduled for extradition/bail review hearing.  Extradition hearing scheduled for August 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Amanda Poznanski in court, defendant Eugene Edward Teasley not in court, in custody.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Poznanski is newly appointed counsel.  She informed the court that a Governor's warrant is not available as of this date.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 25.  Status conference scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley not in court, defendant in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Status Conference.  Prior Counsel retired and no counsel has been appointend for todday court proceedings.  The Court held the hearing without the defendant present due to no counsel being appointed by the public defender's office.  The State is awaiting the Signed Governor's  Warrant.  The clerk sent an email to Public Defender's Office advising of the next court date.  The Court order the matter adjourned to Branch 25.
  Status conference scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Criminal Warrant for Commitment, signed and filed.

Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Eugene Edward Teasley in custody.  Anthony J Moore appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   All parties appeared by video conference.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28.
Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Arizona.
Defendant contested extradition.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
  Per Chief Judge Directive 22-04 effective July 30, 2022, this calendar will be assigned to Judge David Swanson, Branch 11 in Room 316 of the Safety Bldg.  Status conference scheduled for June 24, 2022 at 08:30 am.
